Permissive Model (Blue Oak Council)
fields.description: The model license demonstrates all the characteristics the council looks for in a permissive open software license. Source: [Blue Oak Council](https://blueoakcouncil.org)

fields.name: Permissive Gold (Blue Oak Council)
fields.description: These licenses address patents explicitly, use robust language, and require only simple notice of license terms and copyright notices. Source: [Blue Oak Council](https://blueoakcouncil.org)

fields.name: Permissive Silver (Blue Oak Council)
fields.description: These licenses use robust language but either fail to address patents explicitly or require more than simple notice of license terms and copyright notices. Source: [Blue Oak Council](https://blueoakcouncil.org)

fields.name: Permissive Bronze (Blue Oak Council)
fields.description: These licenses lack important but nonessential elements of permissive open software licenses or impose additional requirements or restrictions, such as BSD-style prohibitions against endorsement and promotion. Source: [Blue Oak Council](https://blueoakcouncil.org)

fields.name: Permissive Lead (Blue Oak Council)
fields.description: These licenses lack one or more essential elements of permissive open software licenses or impose unusually burdensome requirements.  Many use unclear, jocular, or incomplete language. Source: [Blue Oak Council](https://blueoakcouncil.org)

fields.name: Copyleft Weak (Blue Oak Council)
fields.description: Weak copyleft licenses require sharing changes and additions to the licensed software when you give copies to others. Source: [Blue Oak Council](https://blueoakcouncil.org)

fields.name: Copyleft Strong (Blue Oak Council)
fields.description: In addition to the requirements of the weak copyleft licenses, strong copyleft licenses require you to share larger programs that you build with the licensed software when you give copies to others. Source: [Blue Oak Council](https://blueoakcouncil.org)

fields.name: Copyleft Network (Blue Oak Council)
fields.description: In addition to the requirements of strong copyleft licenses, network copyleft licenses require you to share larger programs that you build with the licensed software not just when you give copies to others, but also when you run the software for others to use over the Internet or another network. Source: [Blue Oak Council](https://blueoakcouncil.org)

fields.name: Copyleft Maximal (Blue Oak Council)
fields.description: Maximal copyleft licenses answer the question “When does the license require you to share?” differently than other families. Maximal copyleft licenses require you to share software you make with others, and to license that software alike when you do. Source: [Blue Oak Council](https://blueoakcouncil.org)
